ail investors who want it in the IPO, then they don=E2=80=99t have to go cr=
azy buying it the next day. Robinhood had apparently sold a bit=C2=A0<em>mo=
re=C2=A0</em>stock to retail investors than they wanted, so the stock crack=
ed a bit, but broadly speaking I felt like I had a handle on what happened.=
